      "summary": "jackson-core contains core low-level incremental (\"streaming\") parser and generator abstractions used by Jackson Data Processor. From version 3.0.0 to before version 3.1.0, the UTF8DataInputJsonParser, which is used when parsing from a java.io.DataInput source, bypasses the maxNestingDepth constraint (default: 500) defined in StreamReadConstraints. A similar issue was found in ReaderBasedJsonParser. This allows a user to supply a JSON document with excessive nesting, which can cause a StackOverflowError when the structure is processed, leading to a Denial of Service (DoS). This issue has been patched in version 3.1.0.",
      "severity": "High",
      "updated": "2026-04-06T20:26:35Z",
      "permissions": {},
      "is_source_root": false,
      "is_high_profile": true,
      "high_profile_info": {
         "id": 0,
         "PublicVulnsTblID": 0,
         "VulnId": "XRAY-948994",
         "VulnerabilityTitle": "",
         "ShortDescription": "Stack exhaustion in jackson-core may lead to denial of service when parsing crafted JSON data with excessive nesting.",
         "FullDescription": "[jackson-core](https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-core) is a core library for Jackson that provides low-level streaming JSON input/output functionality.\n",
         "Impact": 5,
         "VulnerabilityType": "Denial of service",
         "Resolution": "",
         "ExtendedImpactReasons": [
            {
               "id": 0,
               "PublicVulnsExtendedTblId": 0,
               "Name": "Exploitation of the issue is only possible when the vulnerable component is used in a specific manner. The attacker has to perform per-target research to determine the vulnerable attack vector",
               "Description": "Exploitation requires the application to parse an untrusted JSON document with excessive nesting, specifically - by loading the untrusted data into the `UTF8DataInputJsonParser` or `ReaderBasedJsonParser` classes.",
               "IsPositive": 1,
               "InsertOrder": 1
            },
            {
               "id": 0,
